<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">PATHING UPGRADES ON TEST, MARCH 8, 2003</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <br>
This is a test server patch mesage only. This does not apply to players on the live servers. <br>
Pathing Changes<br>
<br>
Today we have introduced the first stage of an ongoing project to upgrade the pathing system for EverQuest. <br>
<br>
Of course this means we would like you to keep your eyes open for NPCs doing bad things. NPCs will (should) move a bit differently, that is to be expected. If, for example, you are used to a specific NPC taking a round-about route to get from one place to another and he now takes a more direct route - that's a good thing. <br>
<br>
Bad things would be: <br>
<br>
An NPC that wants to get to you but can't <br>
Pets that can't follow you through a teleporter <br>
Any NPC that takes a much longer path than it should to get to a player (like going away from the target for a bit then heading back) <br>
Any time an NPC doubles back, walking past his destination and then going directly back to it <br>
Any significant 'warping' by NPCs <br>
Any NPCs that defy gravity by walking a few feet above the ground <br>
And any other really odd behavior by NPCs when moving. <br>
<br>
We are aware of current issues with NPCs fleeing (either from Fear or trying to escape death). For now, there is no need to report problems with NPCs fleeing in odd ways. We're working on that one now. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">It is very important that you note the location of the odd behavior, the name of the NPC, what it was doing (just patrolling around or chasing someone it was mad at) and the details of the oddity in your bug reports.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <br>
<br>
Thank you for helping us with this. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:lime;">Thank you for licking my nuzzak.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
- The EverQuest Development Team <br>
